      "source": "Third, the FPGAs are connected to the backplane to talk to other FPGAs in the node, we believe this is to help manage control flow and timing of all the LPUs. The FPGAs also bring extra system DRAM of up to 256GB each. This pool of memory can be used for KVCache if the user wants the entire decode process served by the LPX.",
